# Security Incident Report: Unauthorized Access and Malware Distribution

| Incident ID | Date Identified | Severity | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| INC-2026-001 | June 29, 2026 | High | Investigated / Remediation Pending |

---

## 1. Network Protocol Analysis

During the incident investigation using the network protocol analyzer `tcpdump`, several key network protocols were identified across the TCP/IP layers:

* **DNS (Domain Name System):** Operating at the **Application layer**, DNS was utilized to resolve the domain names (`yummyrecipesforme.com` and `greatrecipesforme.com`) into their respective IP addresses.
* **HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol):** Operating at the **Application layer**, HTTP handled the initial web page requests, transmitted the malicious JavaScript code payload, and facilitated the download of the executable file.
* **TCP (Transmission Control Protocol):** Operating at the **Transport layer**, TCP provided the connection-oriented framework necessary to ensure reliable data packet transmission between client browsers and the web servers.

